# ORIG TITLE    Italians vote in local elections . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Italians are voting in two days of local elections seen as a test for the new coalition government. All eyes are on the mayoral vote in Rome. PM Enrico Letta’s centre-left is fighting ex-PM Silvio Berlusconi’s People of Freedom (PDL) party. The PFL incumbent, Gianni Alemanno, is trailing Democratic Party (PD) candidate Ignazio Marino in the polls. 
